{"parse":{"title":"Peter Auer","pageid":41077434,"revid":839169802,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Peter Auer</b> (born 1954) is professor of <a href=\"/wiki/Germanic_languages\" title=\"Germanic languages\">Germanic</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Linguistics\" title=\"Linguistics\">Linguistics</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Freiburg\" title=\"University of Freiburg\">University of Freiburg</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Freiburg_im_Breisgau\" title=\"Freiburg im Breisgau\">Freiburg im Breisgau</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Germany\" title=\"Germany\">Germany</a>. Auer graduated from the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Constance\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University of Constance\">University of Constance</a> in 1983. He worked at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Hamburg\" title=\"University of Hamburg\">University of Hamburg</a> before going to Freiburg.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Freiburg_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Freiburg-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Auer has authored several monographs and edited numerous collections of scholarly research, including work on <a href=\"/wiki/Code-switching\" title=\"Code-switching\">code-switching</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Contextualization_(sociolinguistics)\" title=\"Contextualization (sociolinguistics)\">contextualization</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Multilingualism\" title=\"Multilingualism\">multilingualism</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Dialectology\" title=\"Dialectology\">dialectology</a>, and other areas of <a href=\"/wiki/Sociolinguistics\" title=\"Sociolinguistics\">sociolinguistics</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Applied_linguistics\" title=\"Applied linguistics\">applied linguistics</a>. He served as the German science foundation's referee for general linguistics from 2000 to 2008.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Freiburg_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Freiburg-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_publications\">Selected publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Peter_Auer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Auer, Peter; Pf\u00e4nder, Stefan (2011). <i>Constructions: Emerging and Emergent</i>. Walter de Gruyter. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-3-11-022908-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-3-11-022908-0\">978-3-11-022908-0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Constructions%3A+Emerging+and+Emergent&amp;rft.pub=Walter+de+Gruyter&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft.isbn=978-3-11-022908-0&amp;rft.aulast=Auer&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rft.au=Pf%C3%A4nder%2C+Stefan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APeter+Auer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Auer, Peter (2007). <i>Style and Social Identities: Alternative Approaches to Linguistic Heterogeneity</i>. Walter de Gruyter. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-3-11-019081-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-3-11-019081-6\">978-3-11-019081-6</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Style+and+Social+Identities%3A+Alternative+Approaches+to+Linguistic+Heterogeneity&amp;rft.pub=Walter+de+Gruyter&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.isbn=978-3-11-019081-6&amp;rft.aulast=Auer&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APeter+Auer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Auer, Peter; Couper-Kuhlen, Elizabeth; Muller, Frank (1999). <i>Language in Time: The Rhythm and Tempo of Spoken Interaction</i>. Oxford University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-19-535516-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-19-535516-1\">978-0-19-535516-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Language+in+Time%3A+The+Rhythm+and+Tempo+of+Spoken+Interaction&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-535516-1&amp;rft.aulast=Auer&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rft.au=Couper-Kuhlen%2C+Elizabeth&amp;rft.au=Muller%2C+Frank&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APeter+Auer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Auer, Peter (1998). <i>Code-Switching in Conversation: Language, Interaction and Identity</i>. Routledge. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-134-60673-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-134-60673-3\">978-1-134-60673-3</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Code-Switching+in+Conversation%3A+Language%2C+Interaction+and+Identity&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-134-60673-3&amp;rft.aulast=Auer&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APeter+Auer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Auer, Peter; Di Luzio, Aldo (1992). <i>The Contextualization of Language</i>. John Benjamins Publishing. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-90-272-5034-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-90-272-5034-6\">978-90-272-5034-6</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Contextualization+of+Language&amp;rft.pub=John+Benjamins+Publishing&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.isbn=978-90-272-5034-6&amp;rft.aulast=Auer&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rft.au=Di+Luzio%2C+Aldo&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APeter+Auer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Auer, Peter (1984). <i>Bilingual Conversation</i>. John Benjamins. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-90-272-2541-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-90-272-2541-2\">978-90-272-2541-2</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Bilingual+Conversation&amp;rft.pub=John+Benjamins&amp;rft.date=1984&amp;rft.isbn=978-90-272-2541-2&amp;rft.aulast=Auer&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APeter+Auer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Peter_Auer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Freiburg-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Freiburg_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Freiburg_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://ww